scrcpy - laptop terminal for android devices

#install particular vertion of hass
pip install homeassistant==0.88.2

npm install pm2@2.10.4 -g

Start at login
pm2 start mosquitto -- -v -c /data/data/com.termux/files/usr/etc/mosquitto/mosquitto.conf
pm2 start node-red --node-args="--max-old-space-size=128" -- -v
pm2 start hass --interpreter=python -- --config /data/data/com.termux/files/home/.homeassistant
pm2 save

pm2 show hass
pm2 logs hass

If you make mistake in pm2 configurationâ€¦
pm2 stop {hass or node-red...}
pm2 delete {hass or node-red...}

nano ~/.bashrc
pm2 resurrect

Home Assistant port 8123
Node-Red port 1880
Mosquitto port 1883

ssh dir:
/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/etc/ssh
set ssh password on termux:
$ passwd (andrei)
New password:
Retype new password:
New password was successfully set.

start sshd in termux, then run: "ssh 192.168.0.222 -p 8022" -> on linux
#to close ssh session press:
Ctrl D
#ssh copy file "sudo" from local to remote:
scp -P 8022 sudo andrei@192.168.0.222:/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin


"LINK" A DIRECTORY FROM THE REMOTE COMPUTER TO AN (EMPTY) DIRECTORY OF THE LOCAL COMPUTER:
Command run on linux PC:
sshfs 176.126.62.77:/data/data/com.termux/files/home/.homeassistant /home/andrei/hass -p 8022
sshfs 192.168.0.178:/data/data/com.termux/files/home /home/andrei/hass -p 8022
Command for unmount:
fusermount -u /home/andrei/hass

/etc/fuse.conf
I had to un-comment:
user_allow_other

Type the following command at the shell prompt to find out top 10 largest file/directories:
# du -a | sort -n -r | head -n 10
directory for mosquitto, hass, node-red log: /home/andrei/hass/.pm2/logs
